Review Description:
This review is on the DeLonghi ESAM5500M Perfecta Digital Super-Automatic Espresso Machine.We ordered and received the black version of this machine. My understanding is that although the metallic blue costs a bit more, the two machines are the same. (This was a birthday present from my wife, but I did help to pick it out.)After pouring over all of the reviews on espresso machines, my wife and I settled on and originally tried to order the 3500 Magnifica, but found that the vendors (we tried two) were unable to fulfill the order saying it was no longer available or they could get it but could not guarantee when it would arrive... So we decided instead to try to order the 5500, and - luckily - had no problem receiving it. Shipment was timely and the packaging was good and solid. Nothing broken, nothing missing.So...how well does it work? First, set up was a breeze. Within 20 minutes, this machine was up and running. The manual recommends making a few tossers to break in the machine, which we did. After that it was a matter of playing with the settings and finding the ideal cup of espresso based on taste.Bottom line, I am very pleased with the results. The cups I've made to date (we've had the machine for about 3 weeks now) have been consistently good. We use the Lavazza beans, and we get good crema in the cups every time. Delicious.Some of the reviews mention that the coffee isn't hot enough...personally, I think it's fine. I wouldn't want my espresso scalding hot. The default setting is medium...if you need it warmer, just move the setting to high. If you need it higher than that, perhaps you're planning on suing the company by spilling some on your lap while driving? If not, you can always heat it in the microwave.The automation in this machine is impressive. It grinds your beans, heats the water and delivers a cup of espresso (or coffee) depending on the settings you make in a matter of seconds. You can set it for water hardness, temperature, size and strength of the coffee, grind settings, auto-on or off if you like...you can also use pre-ground coffee if you prefer (one cup at a time). This machine also comes with a complementary pack of descaler with clear instructions on how to perform the operation.Clean up is a breeze. The instruction manual is comprehensive and clear. If you READ IT you shouldn't have any problems.We haven't had the machine long enough to comment on any maintenance issues, so I may have to add to this sometime in the future depending on how things go. But so far so good.Thanks to my wife for my birthday present. I couldn't be happier.**UPDATE 22 Oct 2013Just did the first descaling and everything went fine. The machine is still operating perfectly with no maintenance issues or problems whatsoever. We do not use milk or cream here, so I cannot comment on the frothing since I've never used it. I've found that the Italian Espresso beans (sold here on Amazon 

Coffee Bean Direct Italian Roast Espresso, Whole Bean Coffee, 5-Pound Bag

  ) work well and taste great. If you like espresso you'll enjoy this machine and the convenience it offers. It holds up to heavy daily use (so far), and it's incredibly easy to operate.
